[line]

[size=4][b]Known Limitations[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][b]Quest ownership[/b]: Quests already accepted by Kliff remain his. The [font=Courier New]![/font] marker and Talk button only appear for the quest owner. [color=#89b4fa]Workaround: accept new quests as your desired character.[/color]
[*][b]Oongka faction quest[/b]: Oongka requires completing "Words Left by the Riverside" faction quest to permanently unlock. Use [url=https://github.com/NattKh/CRIMSON-DESERT-SAVE-EDITOR]CrimsonSaveEditor[/url] Quest Editor to mark it complete, or do the 10-minute quest in-game.
[*][b]Cutscenes[/b]: Story cutscenes still show Kliff's model — these are pre-baked cinematic data
[*][b]Character-locked items[/b]: Some items show a red X when used by the wrong character
[*][b]Chapters 1-2[/b]: Damiane cannot be selected before Chapter 3 — the character switching system itself unlocks during the story tutorial
[*][b]Runtime patch requires x64dbg[/b] each launch until DLL loader is resolved
[/list]

[line]

[size=4][b]Technical Details[/b][/size]

For modders and reverse engineers:

[size=3][b]Runtime Patches (ASI/x64dbg)[/b][/size]
[code]
Patch 1: UIGamePlayControl_Root_ChangeCharacterNotice
  Vtable RVA: 0x48C9C50 (post-update)
  COL RVA:    0x4F0D490
  Patched:    vfunc[4] + vfunc[5] → stub (xor rax,rax; ret)

Patch 2: TrocTrUpdateForbiddenCharacterListAck
  Vtable RVA: 0x4843208 (post-update)
  COL RVA:    0x4EE6080
  Patched:    vfunc[2] (0x981940) → stub
  x64dbg:     disasm [CrimsonDesert.exe+4843218] → xor rax, rax → ret
[/code]

[size=3][b]Data Patches[/b][/size]
[code]
stageinfo.pabgb:     14 entries Func_Damiane_Forbidden → Func_Damiane_Permitted
                     + Func_Oongka_Forbidden → Func_Oongka_Permitted
conditioninfo.pabgb: 29 CheckCharacterKey(Kliff) stripped (+ 2 Damiane, 2 Oongka)
gimmickgroupinfo:    185 CheckCharacterKey(Kliff) stripped
popup HTML:          timeScale=1, progress-time=0, visibility:hidden
[/code]

[size=3][b]Key Discovery: Game is 100% Offline[/b][/size]
Despite using [font=Courier New]TrocTr[/font] packet naming (from Pearl Abyss MMO engine), Crimson Desert is fully offline single-player. The "packets" are internal engine events — no server communication. The forbidden character list is generated locally by the stage system.

[size=3][b]The 15 NonSwitchable Reasons[/b][/size]
[code]
 0. Groggy            5. NotAccompanying   10. ActiveSpecialMode
 1. Dead              6. Battle            11. Target_ImportantQuest
 2. RidingVehicle     7. AlreadyCall       12. Interacting
 3. Stealth           8. Wanted            13. Action
 4. Far               9. ImportantQuest    14. InvalidPosition
[/code]
Our bypass blocks the handler for ALL reasons — not just #9.

[size=3][b]Save File Format[/b][/size]
[code]
Magic: SAVE
Encryption: ChaCha20 (RFC 7539)
Integrity: HMAC-SHA256
Compression: LZ4 HC
Container: PARC (Pearl Abyss Reflect Container)
Location: %LOCALAPPDATA%\Pearl Abyss\CD\save\<steam_id>\slot<N>\save.save
[/code]
Quest completion is stored in encrypted save data. Use [url=https://github.com/NattKh/CRIMSON-DESERT-SAVE-EDITOR]CrimsonSaveEditor[/url] to modify.

[size=3][b]RTTI Scanner[/b][/size]
Vtable addresses are found automatically across game versions via RTTI scanning:
[code]
Scan for ".?AV<classname>@pa@@" → find Type Descriptor
→ find COL (signature=1, references TD RVA)
→ find vtable (COL VA at vtable[-1])
[/code]

